{
  "_description": "Derived matched-data artifact for the section H.2 / G.4 lag test. Drainage dates derived from open CryoSat-2 in-lake elevation series; surface-velocity response from open ITS_LIVE datacubes (box-mean surface speed at the lake centroid). Annual bins (median + 16/84 bootstrap CI + count) are the stable estimator (noise_floor_frac ~1%); quarterly bins are also well resolved (quarterly_scatter_frac ~2-3%). The lag VALUE is not verifiable from this record for two reasons that are NOT velocity noise: (1) the derived sub-annual lag (t* p95 ~0.1 yr) is finer than the finest robust bin (quarterly, 0.25 yr), so a brief post-drainage transient is temporally aliased; and (2) the time-integrated response is below detection (peak ~0.56 sigma), bounding any sustained surge to a few percent. See lag_fit_real.run() for the full logic.",
